news.title: Enforcement directorate attaches assets worth ₹681 crore of Ramprastha group
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has attached Ramprastha real estate group's properties worth over Rs 680 crore in Gurugram due to alleged fraud against homebuyers. This action follows multiple FIRs regarding undelivered flats and plots in projects like Ramprastha City.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers posts ₹616 crore sales in Q1 FY26
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers (KPDL) announced ₹616 crore in sales for Q1 FY26, driven by consistent performance in key projects and a slight increase in sales volume, reaching 0.84 million sq ft. Customer collections remained strong at ₹550 crore. Blackstone's strategic equity infusion, acquiring a 14.3% stake, is expected to further bolster the company's growth prospects.

news.title: Ajmera Realty posts ₹108 crore sales in Q1 FY26
news.para: Ajmera Realty reported ₹108 crore in sales for Q1 FY26, with 63,244 sq ft sold, though project launch delays due to regulatory hurdles impacted performance. Collections surged 42% year-on-year to ₹234 crore, driven by efficient execution.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC forms vigilance squad to check staff negligence in illegal construction cases
news.para: To combat unauthorized construction, PCMC has formed a vigilance squad to monitor staff and ensure swift action against illegal developments. Municipal commissioner Shekhar Singh has warned of disciplinary action for negligence, emphasizing a 24-hour compliance deadline for violators.

news.title: Objection hearings on proposed Purandar airport over; land survey to begin this month
news.para: The Pune administration finished hearing objections regarding the Purandar airport. These objections came from seven villages. A joint land measurement will start this month. The administration will then submit a report to the state government. Some villagers oppose the project. Others want better compensation and jobs. The state aims to acquire land and return some as developed plots.

news.title: Punjab govt set to amend Banur master plan, convert agricultural land to residential zone
news.para: The Punjab government is planning to amend the Banur Master Plan to convert agricultural land into residential zones in response to requests from villagers and gram panchayats. This change, affecting villages around Banur, aims to manage urban growth and meet the rising demand for housing. Public objections are being accepted before a final decision is made.

news.title: Chhattisgarh cabinet approves state capital region authority to boost urban growth
news.para: Chhattisgarh's cabinet has approved the establishment of a State Capital Region authority, mirroring Delhi's NCR, to manage urban growth across Raipur, Durg-Bhilai, and Nava Raipur Atal Nagar. The authority aims to ensure systematic and sustainable development in the face of a projected population of five million by 2031.

news.title: Luxury housing sales surge 85% in H1 2025: Report
news.para: India's luxury housing market experienced substantial growth in the first half of 2025, with sales soaring by 85% to nearly 7,000 units across the top seven cities, fueled by HNIs, ultra-HNIs, and NRIs. Delhi-NCR led the surge, accounting for 57% of total luxury sales, while Mumbai followed with a significant contribution.

news.title: KSH Infra to invest over ₹550 crore in 60-acre logistics park in Tamil Nadu
news.para: KSH Infra is expanding its presence in Tamil Nadu with a Rs 550 crore investment for a new industrial and logistics park in the Sriperumbudur-Oragadam corridor. This follows their initial Rs 450 crore investment in Hosur, bringing their total commitment in the state to over Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: TDR for developing reserved land amenities in Nashik city
news.para: Nashik Municipal Corporation is set to implement a new initiative. Landowners can now develop amenities on reserved land. In return, they will receive Transfer of Development Rights. This move aims to boost public facility development. It also compensates property owners. The NMC has formed a committee to oversee the process.

news.title: Delhi development body to soon launch premium housing scheme
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is set to launch its Premium Housing Scheme 2025, offering 177 flats across Delhi via e-auction. In a recent meeting, DDA also approved reduced amalgamation charges for commercial properties and a lower multiplication factor for commercial property auctions, aiming to boost investment.

news.title: Housing finance companies may log modest Q1 growth, but rate cut to weigh on margins
news.para: Housing finance companies (HFCs) are anticipated to reveal modest earnings for the June quarter, supported by an 8% year-on-year rise in loan disbursals. However, margins are expected to face pressure from bank competition and rate cuts. Provisioning costs might increase due to slower recoveries, potentially leading to flat profit growth after tax.

news.title: Lucknow development body to develop industrial township along Agra expressway
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority is set to develop a 5,610-acre industrial township along the Agra Expressway, aiming to boost investment and create jobs. Covering villages in Sadar and Sarojininagar tehsils, the project includes residential facilities for 2 lakh people. LDA officials met with farmers to discuss land acquisition and address concerns about infrastructure and land record errors.

news.title: CM invites investments in Madhya Pradesh's real estate sector
news.para: Chief Minister Mohan Yadav emphasized the Madhya Pradesh government's commitment to attracting real estate investments by ensuring essential amenities. The Growth Conclave aims to boost urban development, with plans to replicate large markets and expedite metro projects. MoUs were signed for technological integration and infrastructure development, alongside significant housing initiatives under PMAY, benefiting thousands of families.

news.title: Lotus 300 AOA asks Noida authority why it has not registered 228 flats yet
news.para: Lotus 300 AOA takes legal action against Noida Authority. The AOA alleges defiance of Supreme Court orders regarding flat registrations. Despite OC and CC issuance, registration is stalled. The AOA warns of contempt proceedings to protect homebuyers. They cite repeated requests and deposited fees without progress. The legal battle stems from a decade-long struggle and developer delays.

news.title: Mumbai: FIR against Hiranandani Builders for unauthorised excavation and soil erosion in Powai
news.para: Powai police have filed a case against Hiranandani Builders & Developers for allegedly conducting unauthorised excavation near the Powai helipad, leading to soil erosion. The BMC issued a notice to the developer on July 7 regarding the illegal excavation, but the work continued.

news.title: DDA approves reforms to revive Delhi's commercial real estate sector
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has approved significant reforms to boost commercial real estate investment in Delhi. These include reduced amalgamation charges for commercial properties and a lower multiplication factor for property auctions. Additionally, the DDA plans to develop Narela into an educational hub and launch a premium housing scheme for middle- to lower-income groups.

news.title: Unitech Group promoters diverted half of ₹16,000 crore worth buyers' funds for personal use: ED
news.para: The Unitech Group and its promoters are accused by the Enforcement Directorate of diverting nearly half of the ₹16,000 crore received from homebuyers and financial institutions. These funds were allegedly used for personal gains and funneled into various benami companies.

news.title: India’s urban boom an opportunity to build sustainable cities: Former housing secretary
news.para: India envisions urbanization as a chance for growth. By 2047, the urban population may reach 88 crore. Real estate contributes significantly to the economy. Affordable housing shows promising growth. Strategic interventions aim to improve urban life quality.

news.title: Height restrictions put in place within 20 km radius of Noida airport
news.para: Noida International Airport has released an important notice. It concerns construction near the airport. Building or planting trees within 20 km needs permission. The Airport Authority of India must grant a No Objection Certificate. This ensures flight safety. Authorities will check construction plans. Violations could lead to demolition. Compliance is necessary for smooth airport operations.
